        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9712101">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9712101" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9712101.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Accelerator Cable Over-Travel Device</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the over-travel device from the injector pump linkage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut on the accelerator cable which secures the over-travel device on the
                    cable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the over-travel device by unscrewing it from the cable end.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new over-travel device to the cable end.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the accelerator cable to the injector pump linkage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of an assistant, hold the throttle pedal at full travel and determine how
                    much the shaft of the over-travel device has extended from the at rest position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The shaft of the over-travel device should extend 1/4 inch from the at rest position
                    when the throttle pedal is at full travel. To adjust, turn the over-travel device on the threaded
                    end of the accelerator cable (see
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9712101">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After properly adjusting, tighten the jam nut against the over-travel device.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
